@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Frequently Asked Questions";
}

<div class="container mt-5 mb-5">
    <h2 class="text-center mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
    <div class="card shadow-sm p-4">
        <h4 class="mb-3">Warathatul Ambiya Library</h4>

        <div class="mb-4">
            <h5>1. What is Warathatul Ambiya?</h5>
            <p>
                Warathatul Ambiya, meaning <em>“Inheritors of the Prophets,”</em> is a private library in Abuja, Nigeria,
                founded in 1446 AH / 2025 CE. We preserve authentic Islamic literature endorsed by Salafi scholars—primarily
                reliable English translations, with select Arabic and a few Hausa texts. Our aim is to provide sincere seekers
                of knowledge with access to these rare resources, <em>bi idhnillāh</em>.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-4">
            <h5>2. Who can become a member?</h5>
            <p>
                Membership is exclusive to trusted individuals living in Abuja who demonstrate responsibility and a
                commitment to Islamic knowledge. Registration must be completed via our online form using accurate
                personal details.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-4">
            <h5>3. How do I register for membership?</h5>
            <p>
                Visit our website and click the <strong>“Register”</strong> link to submit your application. Our team will review
                your details and notify you via email <a href="mailto:admin@warathatulambiya.com">(admin@warathatulambiya.com)</a>.
                Incomplete or false information will result in rejection.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-4">
            <h5>4. What are the borrowing rules?</h5>
            <p>
                Only approved Abuja-based members may borrow books. Each loan is an <em>amaanah</em>. Members may borrow up to
                two books for three weeks, with a one-week extension option. Books must be returned in original condition
                and must not be passed to others or non-members.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-4">
            <h5>5. What happens if I return a book late or damage it?</h5>
            <p>
                Violations incur fines starting at ₦1000, with ₦1000 added per day. Damaged or lost books may lead to
                suspension or termination of membership and replacement cost liability.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-4">
            <h5>6. Can I borrow books if I live outside Abuja?</h5>
            <p>
                No. Borrowing is restricted to Abuja residents. Non-residents may email
                <a href="mailto:admin@warathatulambiya.com">admin@warathatulambiya.com</a> to discuss alternative engagement.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-4">
            <h5>7. What types of books are available?</h5>
            <p>
                The collection focuses on the Qur’an, Sunnah, and the methodology of the Salaf-us-Sālih, all endorsed
                by Salafi scholars. Most books are English translations, with some Arabic and Hausa titles.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-4">
            <h5>8. How does the recommendation system work?</h5>
            <p>
                Our system suggests texts based on your preferences and borrowing history. Feedback may be collected
                to improve recommendations and enhance user experience.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-4">
            <h5>9. How is my personal information protected?</h5>
            <p>
                We comply with the Nigeria Data Protection Act 2023 (NDPA) and GDPR. Your information is stored
                securely on Microsoft Azure with encryption and is only accessible by authorized administrative staff.
                See our <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for details.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-4">
            <h5>10. Can I access or correct my personal information?</h5>
            <p>
                Yes. Members may email <a href="mailto:admin@warathatulambiya.com">admin@warathatulambiya.com</a>
                to request access or corrections. Include your full name and contact info. GDPR requests are responded
                to within 30 days.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-4">
            <h5>11. How can I contact Warathatul Ambiya?</h5>
            <p>
                Email us at <a href="mailto:admin@warathatulambiya.com">admin@warathatulambiya.com</a> with your name
                and details. We aim to respond promptly, <em>bi idhnillāh</em>.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-2">
            <h5>12. Will the library’s policies change?</h5>
            <p>
                Updates may occur. You’ll be notified via email or the website. Continued use of library services
                means acceptance of any updates to our <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Terms">Terms</a> or
                <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
